# 🚀 EC2 Multi-Server User Setup via SSH (DevOps Practice)
## 📌 Overview
This project demonstrates how to automate user and group creation across multiple EC2 instances using a control server and SSH key-based authentication.
---
## 🧭 Architecture
- **Server 3 (Control Machine)** → Runs the automation script  
- **Server 1 & Server 2 (Target Servers)** → Where users and groups are created 
---
## 🔐 Prerequisites
- EC2 instances are running
- SSH key (`key.pem`) available
- Proper network access (Security Groups configured)
- Sudo access on target servers
 on node chmod 400 key.pem
Test Connectivity
Node test both target servers:
ssh -i key.pem ubuntu@IP
ssh -i key.pem ubuntu@IP

